the <h3>1. Introduction</h3><p>Daily morning awakening and procedures during the first hour a strong influence on all spheres of life. Successful and productive morning leads to a productive and successful day. These morning activities are very closely connected with human self-development and it is important to do them in the morning so as to spend a few minutes during the day is problematic — as a result, work is delayed due to excuses and lack of time.</p><p>Before performing magic am agree with someone to whom you can give a report on your progress.</p><h3>2. Five-step strategy awakening</h3><p><strong>Step 1</strong> Before you go in the evening in bed, clearly specify your intent. Every night before going to bed, form positive expectations from the next morning — thus waking up will be only positive emotions. Your first thought in the morning will be whatever was the last thought in the evening.</p><p><strong>Step 2</strong> — set the alarm away from the bed.</p><p><strong>Step 3 </strong> Brush teeth.</p><p><strong>Step 4</strong> — Drink a glass of water immediately after waking up to get rid of dehydration.</p><p><strong>Step 5</strong> — Wear sportswear, not to pigeonhole exercise.</p><h3>3. "A beautiful Morning" And Six Practices</h3><p>"a Wonderful morning" on six practices of self-development, giving access to powerful internal forces that will help you change any aspect of your life. "Beautiful morning" can last for about 60 minutes. If you are too busy, you can use a shortened version of "perfect morning" — 6 minutes: 1 minute at each practice.</p><h3>Practice 1. Silence (5 minutes)</h3><p>Start the day with calmness, clarity and serenity that will allow you to focus on what's important in life. Do these practices of silence:</p><p>• Meditation</p><p>• Prayer</p><p>• Reflection</p><p>• Deep breath;</p><p>• an Expression of gratitude.</p><h3>Practice 2. Affirmations (5 minutes)</h3><p>Affirmations are positive affirmations for the design and development of our vision to improve any area of life. Affirmations need to read and repeat emotionally, without automaticity and regularly. Affirmations will be updated constantly, because you yourself are updated.</p><p>How to make your own affirmation in five simple steps?</p><p><strong>Step 1.</strong> Decide what you actually want.</p><p><strong>Step 2. </strong>Determine why you want it.</p><p><strong>Step 3.</strong> Decide what kind of person you need to be in order to achieve the desired.</p><p><strong>Step 4. </strong>Determine what you need to do to achieve the desired. What specifically are the steps, timelines and frequency, the better.</p><p><strong>Step 5.</strong> will Include the affirmation inspirational quotes and philosophical thought.</p><h3>Practice 3. Visualization (5 minutes)</h3><p>Three simple steps of the visualization:</p><p><strong>Step 1.</strong> Prepare. Tune in and comfortably sit down.</p><p><strong>Step 2.</strong> Draw in the imagination of what you actually want to. Visualize your most important goals, secret desires, and wildest dreams. Feel, sense and see them. Engage all the senses. Rewind thoughts forward to see how you have achieved results.</p><p><strong>Step 3.</strong> Imagine what you must become and what it needs. To vision could be realized, visualize yourself already living the life of a man who you should be.</p><h3>Practice 4. Exercise (20 minutes)</h3><p>Do your favorite exercise for increasing energy, health and confidence. Fit gym, Jogging, yoga and other exercises that will make you cheer.</p><h3>Practice 5. Reading (20 minutes)</h3><p>This is a direct source of knowledge, ideas and building a strategy for success. Read at least 10 pages a day. Remember the ultimate goal of reading when you take up a book: what do you want to?</p><h3>Practice 6. Journaling (5 minutes)</h3><p>Keep a diary for clearing the brain, identify new ideas, repetition of the lessons learned and assessment and recognition of progress, and then after a year re-read my notes. Re-read the diary and as you read write down on a piece of "lessons Learned" and "New commitments."</p><p><strong>How to enter the diary:</strong></p><p>1. Select a format: digital or traditional.</p><p>2. Select tool: a notebook or program / online service.</p><p>3. Decide what you want to write about your goals, dreams, plans, commitments, the lessons learned. List what you are grateful for, acknowledge achievements, specify where you want to improve, and describe specific actions.</p>